<P>
   NY-CHILD-DEPORT (New York) _ A 16-year-old boy originally from
Trinidad is to appear in federal court Tuesday for a deportation
hearing. The boy came to the United States illegally with his
parents at age 3; at some point his father left the mother and
married an American, thus naturalizing father and son. The boy was
part of a chess team that went to Russia for a tournament two years
ago, and the trip put him back on the Immigrations and
Naturalization Service radar screen. He then got a letter telling
him to appear in federal court on Aug. 22, and that he would be
deported. By John Sullivan.
</P>
