<SLUG> BC-FBC-USCNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RIDEAUX EXPECTS TO BE EXTREMELY BUSY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVINE, Calif. _ Darrell Rideaux is officially listed as a
!ital!co!off!- starter at cornerback. However, he will be
!ital!the!off! starter when USC plays Penn State on Sunday, and he
already knows what to expect when the Nittany Lions see the
diminutive 5-foot-8 sophomore in the secondary.
</P>
<P>
   ``When they see me, it will be audible (at) Rideaux,'' he said.
``I expect a lot of balls coming my way early. The first couple
days of hell week, our offense did that.''
</P>
<P>
   It's tempting for an offense to test Rideaux. The other
cornerback, Kris Richard, is 6 feet, so it makes sense for a
quarterback to go at the shorter player.
</P>
<P>
   ``The difference is that this year I've been through the fire,''
Rideaux said.
</P>
<P>
   This will be his third straight start after filling in the final
two games of the 1999 season for the injured Antuan Simmons.
</P>
<P>
   Rideaux fended off a challenge from Chris Cash, considered one
of the top junior college cornerbacks in the country last season.
</P>
<P>
   ``Each year, USC recruits the best in the country,'' Rideaux
said. ``I was considered to compete for a starting job. We don't
care about that. Obviously, Chris has strengths and I have
strengths.''
</P>
<P>
   Worse than expected: Senior offensive lineman Trevor Roberts
will miss the Kickoff Classic with a strained foot, and there is
now some concern he might not be ready for the Sept. 9 game against
Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll be back,'' Roberts said. ``They can't keep me out that
long.''
</P>
<P>
   Redshirt freshman Lenny Vandermade will start in place of
Roberts at left guard.
</P>
<P>
   Knight leaves: Linebacker Darryl Knight, the younger brother of
former USC players Ryan and Sammy Knight, has quit the team
``because of personal issues and is a little unsure'' whether he
will play football again, Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Knight has fallen off the depth chart and watched his role
decrease since last spring to the point where he played on the
scout team.
</P>
<P>
   Freshmen on road: Hackett said he will take eight true freshmen
to the Kickoff Classic, although it is a ``one-game decision,'' and
some players could redshirt.
</P>
<P>
   Tight ends Gregg Guenther of Taft High and Alex Holmes of
Harvard- Westlake, quarterback Matt Cassel of Chatsworth, wide
receiver Keary Colbert, offensive lineman Joe McGuire, tailback
Chris Howard, strong safety Matt Grootegoed and defensive tackle
Kenechi Udeze made the travel squad.
</P>
<P>
   Guenther, who missed most of last week with a sore back, has
practiced this week and is available to play.
</P>
<P>
   Don't drink the water: The Trojans ordered plenty of bottled
water for the game to prevent a problem they encountered in the
1996 Kickoff Classic: About 20 players came down with flu after
drinking contaminated tap water at Giants Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Jersey switch: USC will wear its home cardinal jerseys against
Penn State even though the Trojans are the visiting team. Penn
State has opted for its white jerseys because of the heat. The
current forecast for East Rutherford, N.J., on Sunday is partly
cloudy with a high of 82 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   Game captains: Linebacker Zeke Moreno, defensive tackle Ennis
Davis, tailback Petros Papadakis and center Eric Denmon have been
named game captains. Simmons, who is redshirting after having a
stomach tumor removed, is a ``special captain,'' according to
Hackett.
</P>
</TEXT>
