   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-RAIDERS (Oakland, Calif.) _ Among the underpublicized
reasons Richard Nixon was driven from office with pitchforks were
his periodic attempts to phone in plays to then-Washington Redskins
coach George Allen. Unlike visiting China or helping cover up a
burglary, that sort of thing is best left to the professionals. On
the other hand, this seems like the perfect time to drop a quick
one in Jon Gruden's in-basket over at Raiders Galactic
Headquarters. By RAY RATTO.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-JACOBS (Oakland, Calif.) _ Even after winning the 1,500 and
5,000 meters at last month's Olympic Track and Field Trials,
Oakland's Regina Jacobs knew she would not be running both events
in the Sydney Olympics. The question was which one she'd pick.
Jacobs provided an answer Tuesday. The four-time Olympian and
Stanford University graduate opted for the 1,500 over the longer
race, even though she is the American record-holder at 5,000. By
JOHN CRUMPACKER.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BRONCOS-SLUR (Denver) _ Free safety Eric Brown said this
week he and several other black Denver Broncos felt mixed emotions
when a published report indicated that an unidentified white player
had accused linebacker Bill Romanowski of using a racial slur. By
TOM ORSBORN.
