<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Of rats and men: `Survivor' summer
 &HT;    By Drew Jubera
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It started May 31 as a summer fill-in; it ends tonight, 12 weeks
later, as a summer phenom. Here's an episode-by-episode look at how
the legacy and the lunacy grew:
</P>
<P>
   Episode 1
</P>
<P>
   America gets new vernacular: ``immunity challenge,'' ``tribal
council,'' ``Jeff Probst.'' B.B., uber bully coot, makes Rudy look
like a diva. Early strategy: Kill the old-timers first. Senior
Sonja trips during immunity challenge, voted clean off.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 15.5 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 2
</P>
<P>
   Ramona throws up. Richard notes he's gay. First immunity
challenge to get our attention: eating live beetle larvae. Gervase
balks, Stacey gulps, B.B. walks.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 18.1 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 3
</P>
<P>
   Turning point: Castaways eat rat. Tastes like: rat.
Larvae-eating Stacey stunned by ouster.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 23.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 4
</P>
<P>
   Looks like sunstroke: Greg makes phone calls from coconut shell;
Sean builds ``Gilligan''-like bowling alley. Rich-Sue-Kelly
alliance forms (Rudy holds out). Ramona declares herself well _ and
then gets booted. ``Too little too late,'' Jenna says of Lazarus
act.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 24.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 5
</P>
<P>
   ``At this point, it's all about sex,'' island cutie Colleen coos
of private getaways with Coconut Greg. Bible Boy Dirk gets the
heave, thanks Jesus, sports sarong on David Letterman's show.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 24 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 6
</P>
<P>
   Richard drops shorts (viewers grateful for digital-blurring
technology), tribe cooks dog food (beats larvae), Gervase and Joel
turn chauvinist. S'long, Joel.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 24.5 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 7
</P>
<P>
   Down to single, 10-castaway tribe. Richard's alliance _ Rudy's
in _ flexes Popeye-sized muscle. Gretchen's a goner.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 24.5 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 8
</P>
<P>
   Off-island hijinks: CBS Web site mistakenly posts that night's
episode summary in afternoon, revealing Greg is toast. He is.
Hacker claims he invaded site to learn Gervase is the
million-dollar survivor (see Episode 10).
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 26.1 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 9
</P>
<P>
   Richard celebrates birthday in ... his birthday suit. We thought
larvae looked bad. Rudy thinks dames have gone lesbian. Jenna's
sent packing.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 27.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 10
</P>
<P>
   It's ``Lord of the Flies'' now. Kelly rues evil alliance
membership (``I feel like Luke Skywalker,'' she says of Richard
luring her to Dark Side). Gervase's girlfriend has baby. He
dispenses cigars, looks like a million bucks _ until council votes
him off.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 27.4 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 11
</P>
<P>
   Kelly schemes against new friend Susan. Can't out-scheme a
schemer: Kelly's next to go _ then wins immunity challenge. Colleen
is bye-bye.
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 28 million.
</P>
<P>
   Episode 12
</P>
<P>
   Finally, mud wrestling: five survivors roll in volcanic mud pit
for reward challenge. Kelly wins beer, then wins immunity
challenge. No more Sean. Sighs Richard, ``This maintaining some
kind of a thumb on all these peoples' personalities that I care
very little about is exhausting.'' For him? Or us?
</P>
<P>
   Viewers: 28.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   _Drew Jubera djubera(at)ajc.com
</P>
