<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0819 -- LIQUID OF LIFE _ Just try to imagine a
kitchen without water. No boiled pasta or iced tea; no soup stock
or steamed rice.
</P>
<P>
   Nothing as pure and wet to quench a thirst of drought
proportions. Water is the most underrated cooking ingredient there
is. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   Sidebar on bottled water. Art includes a 2 column color photo, 2
column glossary on bottled waters with photo of man selling water
in glass.
</P>
<P>
   Recipes that just couldn't work without water. Art includes a 2
column color photo of peach recipe.
</P>
<P>
   How teenager prepares meals for busy family. Includes a 1 column
box with teenager's recipe for crunchy baked chicken.
</P>
<P>
   END OF COXNET PAGE
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-SMOKED _ About 10 years ago I cooked in a restaurant where
the owner, perhaps unwisely, encouraged me to indulge in whatever
cooking obsession was gripping me at the moment. I discovered
stovetop smoking. And some really delicious things started to come
out of the kitchen. (Kessler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-SMOKED-RECIPES _ Recipe page to go with the Smoked story
centerpieced on AJC weekly food section. (Kessler, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
