<P>
   WRIGHT-LIKE _ ATLANTA _ Talk to Stephen Dull and Bill Baites
about their renovation, and within minutes the inevitable occurs:
The house repeatedly is referred to as if it were a Frank Lloyd
Wright. Wright this, Wright that _ which is not right. Well, not
entirely anyhow. The postwar Prairie Style house in Collier Hills
was designed in 1960 by Atlanta architect Robert Green, who was one
of Wright's last apprentices. But the pride these homeowners take
in its design _ and recent award-winning preservation _ could not
be greater had the 20th-century master drawn the plans himself.
(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   NUTS-BOLTS-COLUMN _ Most people have houses full of natural wood
furnishings, but very few people are completely sure about how to
care for them. That's why it's not uncommon for furniture owners to
make routine maintenance mistakes that lessen the beauty of their
wood over time. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 25. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
