<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SURVIVOR-FINALFOUR23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Who will win? Gauging the odds on `Survivor'
 &HT;    By Drew Jubera and Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   They began as 16 and now they are a quartet, ready to treat
America to a chorus of four-part disharmony. Here's the lowdown on
the ``Survivor'' Final Four:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Richard Hatch, 39, Rhode Island corporate trainer.
</P>
<P>
   In a nutshell: The man with a plan. Manipulative, openly gay,
makes Machiavelli look like Mother Teresa.
</P>
<P>
   Memorable moments: Going nekkid, doing a victory dance when he
won an immunity challenge.
</P>
<P>
   Who plays him in the movie? Kevin Spacey.
</P>
<P>
   Why he'll win: Remember that conniving, back-stabbing colleague
who got an undeserved promotion and nobody could figure out why?
That's Richard, the Miles Drentell of Pulau Tiga.
</P>
<P>
   Why he'll lose: The island's most despised resident. If it comes
down between him and anybody (with the possible exception of
Susan), he loses.
</P>
<P>
   Chances: His naked ambition works against him. Except ... he may
have one last trick up his sleeve (if he had a sleeve).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Kelly Wigles-
</P>
<P>
   worth, 23, Nevada river guide.
</P>
<P>
   In a nutshell: Waffling lucky duck.
</P>
<P>
   Memorable moment: Boasting that she would clobber landlubber
Gervase in a canoe race, then losing.
</P>
<P>
   Who plays her in the movie? Sandra Bullock.
</P>
<P>
   Why she'll win: Everything's going her way. Every time she was
about to be booted, she won the immunity challenge.
</P>
<P>
   Why she'll lose: No one can be this lucky for that long.
</P>
<P>
   Chances: 50-50. If she's immunized until the final two, probably
beats Richard or Susan.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Rudy Boesch, 72, ex-Navy SEAL from Virginia Beach, Va.
</P>
<P>
   In a nutshell: Scrappy, politically incorrect old coot.
</P>
<P>
   Memorable moment: Spreading suntan oil on Richard's back,
although he's wondered what his Navy friends would say about his
having a gay friend.
</P>
<P>
   Who plays him in the movie? Richard Farnsworth.
</P>
<P>
   Why he'll win: Went from being the island's biggest irritant to
sentimental choice when paired with almost anybody who's left.
</P>
<P>
   Why he'll lose: After a month in the sun, can barely remember
his own name.
</P>
<P>
   Chances: Consensus favorite. After surviving early attempts to
exile him, has flown under radar while the rest picked each other
off. Crazy like a fox.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Susan Hawk, 39, Wisconsin truck driver.
</P>
<P>
   In a nutshell: Blue-collar brawler, future WWF calendar girl.
</P>
<P>
   Memorable moment: Probed by ``Tiki Jeff'' Probst at a tribal
council, she says, ``Alliance? What alliance? Who, me?''
</P>
<P>
   Who plays her in the movie? Kathy Bates.
</P>
<P>
   Why she'll win: Tough, insensitive, untrustworthy schemer.
</P>
<P>
   Why she'll lose: Tough, insensitive, untrustworthy schemer.
</P>
<P>
   Chances: Could be the dark horse behind Rudy, if she can
outmaneuver Richard.
</P>
