<P>
   TEEN-VEGETARIAN _ I have a young friend who decided to become a
vegetarian when she was in high school. But after sharing many
meals with her family, I began to jokingly refer to her as a
pastatarian. So many young vegetarians -- and some older ones, too
-- use the term to distinguish what they don't eat not what they
do. Families with teenage vegetarians may want to check out a new
book by Lauren Butts, a 16-year-old Oregon girl who has gathered
her favorite recipes for such favorites as wraps, pizzas,
``burgers'' and more in the ideal guidebook for the teenage
vegetarian. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
