episode. By Caryn James.
</P>
<P>
   With
</P>
<P>
   TV-SURVIVOR-IMPACT (Undated) _ Has the success of ``Survivor''
changed the TV landscape? By Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   Editors, these two stories will be late.
</P>
<P>
   MOSES-GOSPEL-MUSIC (Boston) _ Walter Robinson, a composer from
Cambridge, Mass., has spent the last four years piecing together
``Moses,'' which tells the Old Testament story of the liberation of
the Israelites from slavery through black music and dance. Hundreds
of blacks and Jews, from professional singers to children in
choirs, have contributed to ``Moses,'' which has had about two
dozen performances in synagogues, churches and theaters. By Julie
Flaherty.
</P>
<P>
   BEAUTY-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ In ``Another Beauty,'' by the
distinguished Polish poet Adam Zagajewski, Zagajewski locates
himself at an opposite end from the French-Romanian E.M. Cioran,
compiler of an epigrammatic encyclopedia of despair. Zagajewski, to
the contrary, can write only out of happiness. Reviewed by Richard
Eder.
</P>
