r e BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE24     08-23 0351
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   With continuing financial problems, rumors are hot that World
Championship
</P>
<P>
   Wrestling is ready to make some cuts.
</P>
<P>
   Starting Oct. 23, WCW will tape Thunder on the same night and
location as Monday Nitro live in an attempt to cut production
costs. WCW also hopes it will increase attendance since Nitro shows
have struggled to fill 5,000-6,000 seats recently.
</P>
<P>
   Estimates have the WCW losing nearly $80 million and past
leadership has talked about, but failed, to cut the
long-in-the-tooth wrestling talent.
</P>
<P>
   And Thunder shows have had crowds that can't meet the expenses
of the production crew, not to mention the cost of the wrestlers.
</P>
<P>
   Brad Siegel, the Turner executive who oversees WCW, is expected
to drop big-money, low-return wrestlers such as Lex Luger, Diamond
Dallas Page, Buff Bagwell and Kaynon.
</P>
<P>
   The hope is to drop $10 million to $15 million in salary before
parent company Time Warner's merger with America Online is
finalized in January, with a lot of cuts after WCW's fiscal year
ends Oct. 31.
</P>
<P>
   In the ring one of the big changes for WCW is the return of
Goldberg as a face. He did not go over with the fans as a heel and
after months of complaining
</P>
<P>
   he has returned to his face role. Kevin Nash is stepping into a
top heel role.
</P>
<P>
   The WWF's push to register voters has resulted in 20,000 new
voters, according to wwf.com. Fans can sign up at house shows or at
WWFvote.com.
</P>
<P>
   A couple of interesting items from the wwf.com Jim Ross Report:
``Stone Cold Steve Austin update: Steve is about 60 days away from
return. Austin weighs about 253 pounds and is looking to return at
around 245-247. The Rattlesnake and Debra plan on getting married
later this month also.''
</P>
<P>
   Ross also had news on The Big Show, who will be out for a few
weeks with a herniated disk in his back.
</P>
<P>
   When he returns he will be assigned to Ohio Valley Wrestling
(OVW) in Louisville, Ky., to lose some weight.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
