<SLUG> BC-VICTORIA-PRINCIPAL-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VICTORIA SHARES HER SECRETS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By MIKI TURNER 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Victoria Principal, who first rose to fame as Pamela Ewing on
the addictive prime-time soap ``Dallas,'' returns to television
this fall in Aaron Spelling's campy sudser ``Titans.'' Principal,
50, plays nightclub owner and rich divorcee Gwen Williams. Gwen is
very different from Pam Ewing, but Principal has changed a great
deal, too. The Principal is definitely in charge now.
</P>
<P>
   QUESTION: You're 50, and you look fabulous. What is your secret?
</P>
<P>
   ANSWER: I think that America, unlike Europe and many other
cultures, has relegated women after the age of 35 to pigeonholing.
You are no longer sexy, you are just a mother, a wife, an ex-wife,
or just a professional or just single. And guess what? We are so
many things. Watch out, world!
</P>
<P>
   Q: Have you always had a high degree of self-confidence?
</P>
<P>
   A: I think that it's about life experiences and wisdom. I think
that I was not a secure person at 25 at all. But I think 25 years
later, I have a certain sense of self through life experiences,
which gives me confidence because I've lived it. And I hope at 60
and 70 and 80 and 90 that I'm wearing purple!
</P>
<P>
   Q: Why purple?
</P>
<P>
   A: Why not?
</P>
<P>
   Q: When you woke up on the morning of your 50th birthday, what
were you feeling?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``I couldn't wait to see the jewelry. My husband made my 50th
birthday really, really fun. He invited all my friends, and there
was a party that lasted longer than my life. And there was a ring
that put a big smile on my face. But most of all, I asked everyone
not to bring gifts, and what everyone did was bring handmade cards.
I have a special box with all the cards in it that I will have for
the rest of my life. The cards are affectionate, funny, serious,
loving, and some of them are like journals chronicling 30 years of
friendship. It was wonderful.
</P>
<P>
   Q: They always say men grow wiser as they get older. Does the
same hold true for women?
</P>
<P>
   A: That depends on the person and that varies from person to
person. I think life is a gift, and I intend to celebrate every
decade of it.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Are there things that you now do at 50 that you wouldn't have
dared do at 20, 30 or 40?
</P>
<P>
   A: When I was 20, I would walk into a room and wonder if anyone
liked me. And now when I walk into a room I wonder, ``Who do I
like?''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
