<P>
   BUYER'S-EDGE _ Long gone are the days when it was cool to set up
your computer in a dank, musty corner of the basement on an
easy-to-assemble wobbly desk from Kmart. As more people get home
PCs, the computer is attaining the status of the television set in
American homes. By freelancer Mary Jo DiLonardo. Originally
appeared in Personal Technology May 7. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTOS and LAYOUT.
