<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0819 _ LIQUID OF LIFE _ Just try to imagine a
kitchen without water. No boiled pasta or iced tea; no soup stock
or steamed rice.
</P>
<P>
   Nothing as pure and wet to quench a thirst of drought
proportions. Water is the most underrated cooking ingredient there
is. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
