<P>
   BOOKNOTES _ Robert Morgan's novel ``Gap Creek'' and Janisse
Ray's ``Ecology of a Cracker Childhood'' are this year's winners of
the Southern Book Critics Circle Awards for fiction and nonfiction.
. . . What do publishers read on vacation? Publishing Trends
Newsletter did an informal survey and found most executives were
reading books from other publishing houses. But the VP at
Scholastic, J.K. Rowling's publisher, is listening to Harry Potter
on tape as ``background music'' while he reads Michael Ondaatje's
``Anil's Ghost.'' (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE _ With continuing financial problems, rumors
are hot that World Championship Wrestling is ready to make some
much needed cuts. The first thing they will do is tape the Thunder
on the same night as they run Monday Nitro live. (Allen, Cox News
Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-MAT _ Video of the week: ``Beyond the Mat'' wrestling
