<P>
   SCIENCE-MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   DIABETES _ Diabetes rose by 33 percent in the past decade, and
37 percent in Georgia, according to a new CDC study in the
September issue of Diabetes Care. Researchers say the main factor
is obesity, which is also affecting more of the American
population. Those diagnosed with diabetes are younger, with a 70
percent increase found in people ages 30-39. (Lore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH PHOTO.
