<P>
   NY-SUBWAY-OBSESSION (New York) _ If Darius McCollum were a
millionaire, he might be excused as an eccentric. If he were a
genius, allowances probably would be made as well. But McCollum is
neither. And his unusual problem _ his obsession, as he calls it _
has gotten him in so much trouble that people aren't even laughing
anymore. Since he was a high school freshman, McCollum, 35, has
been in and out of jail for masquerading as a New York City transit
worker. New York is a city where train buffs rank among the
quirkiest. Even so, the authorities say McCollum towers above the
best of them, and he has repeatedly fooled riders, subway employees
and the police into believing he belongs in transit blues. By Dean
E. Murphy. (The story has moved in ``a'' news file.) 1,800 words.
