<P>
   BIOTECH (Undated) _ As a young biotechnology company in 1986,
OSI Pharmaceuticals agreed to use its expertise in genes and
molecular biology to help Pfizer Inc. discover new drugs for
cancer. OSI agreed to receive a royalty of around 5 percent on
sales of any drugs that made it to market. Now OSI has a chance to
make a much better deal. In order to win antitrust clearance for
its acquisition of Warner-Lambert, Pfizer recently gave back to OSI
full rights to one of the drugs from their collaboration. By Andrew
Pollack.
</P>
