</P>
<P>
   Then, after they broke up, things really got intense.
</P>
<P>
   Breiman approaches the usual ``Why are guys so weird and can't I
keep one?'' neurotics with a beguiling, shambling earthiness. The
film's title is not deceptive; when at a loss for how to express a
worrisome feeling, Kate unerringly goes carnal with often
uproarious consequences. Just one small but telling example: Of all
the jokey tongue-kissing that we've been subjected to in this
