<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Thursday, Aug. 24, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Mary Downes on the national-foreign desk at (206)
448-8158.
</P>
<P>
   TWA-CRASH (Washington) _ The National Transportation Safety
Board says that Boeing's design and design philosophy _ that it
could design all ignition sources away from fuel tanks and that air
conditioning packs could be place below the tank without venting _
contributed to the crash of Paris-bound TWA Flight 800.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``w'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Detroit) _ Seattle Mariners, riding a one-game
winning streak, take on Detroit in second game of series.
</P>
<P>
   By John Hickey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
