<P>
   Drain marinade from portobell
</P>
<P>
   After dining with her family several times, I began to tease
her, calling her a ``pastatarian'' rather than a vegetarian, as her
meals seemed to consist largely of pasta and cheese, with
occasionally a token broccoli floret or two.
</P>
<P>
   Teenagers (and older folks) choose vegetarianism for a variety
of reasons, from health concerns to ethical decisions to simply
wanting to fit in with friends who are vegetarians.
</P>
<P>
   But for far too many teenagers (and some older folks), the term
vegetarian refers much more to what they don't eat rather than what
they do eat.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's something more to being a vegetarian than pulling
pepperoni off the pizza,'' said Lauren Butts, 16, author of ``OK,
So Now You're a Vegetarian'' (Broadway Books, $12.95). To aid new
vegetarians, Butts, working with nutritionist Donna Shields, offers
practical information, from the vegetarian food guide pyramid to a
glossary of terms like millet (a grain) and vega
</P>
