13.4 million shares, more than twice the company's three month
average. Aside from the Patriots deal, no other company news was
released Wednesday, CMGI officials said.
</P>
<P>
   A former mathematics major who founded CMGI when he took a small
textbook direct marketing company known as College Market Group
public in 1994, Wetherell is seen as having a particular genius for
on online marketing.
</P>
<P>
   But when asked whether CMGI would buy naming rights for the Red
Sox new ballpark, Wetherall, a fanatic baseball player in his
youth, demurred.``I think there will be a backlash to renaming
Fenway Park,'' he said. ``Like a lot of people, I think it would be
great if the team could find someone who wants to buy the naming
rights but will keep the name. ''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
