<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHOPPING-GUIDE24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have been a user of English Leather men's products for
years. Specifically, I'm looking for underarm stick deodorant and
after-shave lotion.
</P>
<P>
   _ Maurice Glatzer, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   And another request: I am wondering if English Leather Deodorant
Stick has been discontinued or is it just hard to find?
</P>
<P>
   _ William Lee, Smyrna, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Yet another request: I am trying to locate English Leather
Deodorant Stick. It is the only deodorant soothing to my skin. I am
desperate because I am down to my last one.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sam Ingram, Dacula, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   And a final plea: I am looking for the deodorant English
Leather. I have used this for years and suddenly it has disappeared
from the market.
</P>
<P>
   _ Ralph Rutherford, Doraville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Lovers of English Leather can soon be smelling like their
favorite scent. This longtime men's classic, composed of mossy,
woody and leather notes, is sold through Classic Edition
Fragrances. The traditional 2.75-ounce Deodorant Stick is $4. The
company also sells English Leather Musk and Lime Deodorant Sticks
for $4.50 each. To buy, call 1-888-254-5060. You can also order
English Leather after-shave and cologne at this number.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Recently I heard about a tradition of using cake charms in a
bridal luncheon cake. Each bridesmaid pulls a charm from the cake
with a ribbon. And each charm has a special meaning. I've contacted
bridal shops but haven't been able to find them. Any idea where I
can look?
</P>
<P>
   _ Kellie Hewitt, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Those Victorians knew how to party. Ribbon pulling is an
event for the bride to share with her bridesmaids at a luncheon or
at the wedding reception. The custom has been passed down for
generations. Tiny charms attached to ribbons are frosted into a
wedding cake, allowing the ribbons to flow from the side of cake.
Each bridesmaid pulls a ribbon, then discovers what her charm
means.
</P>
<P>
   An anchor symbolizes hope and adventures in life; the clover, a
life of good luck; a flower, a life of flourishing love; the heart,
a life with everlasting love; the wedding ring, a wedding date
soon; and the teddy bear, a happy home full of life. The
silver-plated charms from the Anna Rose collection are available at
Cake Art, 5296 Memorial Drive, Stone Mountain (404-294-5005). The
kit is $23.99 and includes six charms, ribbons, and a booklet
explaining the significance of each charm.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I would like to know if Red Diamond coffee is sold anywhere
in metro Atlanta. Or can it be ordered directly from the company? I
know it is still very popular in Alabama.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sandra B. Watts, Doraville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Crank up the ole percolator. Your Red Diamond coffee is
available at several Wal-Mart Supercenters, including the location
at 1355 East-West Connector in Austell (770-863-9300). A 12-ounce
bag of whole beans and the 12-ounce auto-drip vaccum brick are
$1.98 each. Piggly Wiggly stores also carry Red Diamond. Or, order
it directly from the Alabama-based company at 1-800-292-4651.
Prices for each item are $2.65. Other flavors include Latin Magic
Coffee &AMP; Chicory. This Alabama coffee was first made in 1906 by
William Fitz Donovan, who searched for the perfect name. He
reasoned that since a red diamond is the jewel unsurpassed in
quality, it was the right name and standard for his coffee. Today,
the company also produces tea bags.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am trying to find Mount Vernon Salad Dressing, which I used
to buy at Winn-Dixie. It's distributed by Hannah's Sweet Dressings
in Chattanooga.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jan Morgan, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: How sweet it is. Although these dressings are practically
impossible to find in metro Atlanta, you can pick them up in Publix
stores in South Georgia, Savannah, Hilton Head, S.C., and in North
Florida. Also, in Chattanooga, Winn-Dixie, Fresh Market and BiLo
stores stock these products. But you can order the dressings ($2.95
for an 8-ounce bottle or $36 for a 12-bottle case plus shipping) at
423-266-0290. Flavors include Sweet Celery, Orange Poppyseed, Blue
Onion, Greek Vinaigrette, French Onion and Razzmataz Vinaigrette.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have been trying to locate appliance covers for a toaster,
blender and electric mixer. I have looked everywhere and can't find
them. Could you please help?
</P>
<P>
   _ Carolyn Boswell, Newnan, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We've got you covered. Appliance covers in a red apple
pattern banded in green are available through the Blair Shoppe Gift
Gallery catalog. Toaster, blender, mixer, can opener and
bread-maker covers are priced from $7.95 to $12.95 each. To order:
1-800-458-2000. Appliance covers in a multicolored fruit print are
also available at Linens 'N Things, 2900 Peachtree Road N.E.,
Atlanta (404-816-2700). The blender cover is $7.99; the mixer or
coffeepot cover is $9.99; a can opener cover is $5.99.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
