</HEADLINE>
  
 &HT;    Editors: &HT;    The following story is an added starter on The New York Times
front page. It has moved in ``e'' category.
 &HT;    
 &HT;    
 &HT;    TV-SURVIVOR-IMPACT (Undated) _ With parties being thrown to
celebrate it, news organizations scheduling special coverage and
viewers all over the nation waiting in near breathless
anticipation, a summer television series ended Wednesday night
accompanied by the kind of attention usually reserved for massive
national events, on the scale of the Super Bowl or the Academy
Awards. And all of it to learn that one contestant, Richard Hatch,
39, a corporate trainer from Newport, R.I., had managed to win $1
million dollars by enduring a made-for-television survival test on
a island off the coast of Borneo. By Bill Carter. 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
</P>
